values:
Unnecessary people, we're 
Composed of men misused, 
Of women panicking, of weird
ideas. We're confused, 
Naive, but easy to appal, 
We run for our pride, 
Since we are nihil for them all 
Who shan't but will decide. 
Since any utterance is void 
of sense, there's nothing more 
To it. I'll run and run, my Lord, 
Till we're beyond the war.
